message.content:
A 'redshank' is a medium-sized wading bird of the sandpiper family.
It has long red legs that contrast with its brownish-grey body.
The bill is thin and slightly curved, with a reddish base.
The eyes are dark and set back on the head.
Its wings are pointed and it has a distinctive white "V" shape on its back when in flight.
Redshanks are commonly found in marshes, wet meadows and coastal estuaries.
They are known for their loud and distinctive shrill calls.
